Inside Cocaine Wars

Health-Medical Documentary hosted by Johnathan Booth, published by National Geographic in 2012 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Inside Cocaine Wars
From the Caribbean to Colombia, elite cops battle billion-dollar drug cartels to stop the flow of cocaine before it hits American shores. They face a brutal, ingenious foe - in a conflict where the stakes run into the billions but life itself comes very cheap. Whether stalking drug mules in Colombian airports or tracking cocaine speedboats roaring through Caribbean seas, Inside Cocaine Wars plunges you into action alongside American DEA agents doing jobs most of you don't even know exist. Each week, you're given unique, DEA access never granted before: from the drug mules that are often forced or trapped into trafficking drugs for gang members, to the hunt for the Columbian drug cartels' latest secret weapon - the elusive cocaine submarines. This is a war everyone's heard of, but few have every truly seen: until now.


1)  Airport Sting 
Join a crack team of DEA agents as they prowl the terminals of Colombia's El Dorado International Airport in search of cocaine mules.

2)  Drug Speedboats 
DEA agents track one of the most elusive drug cartel targets of all - the cocaine speedboat, packed with up to two tons of Colombian cocaine.

3)  Narco Sub Mystery 
DEA agents hunt Colombia's elusive cocaine submarine that can pack around seven tons of coke as cargo and smuggle it out of Colombia underwater.

4)  Drug Mules 
DEA agents search for human mules that carry cocaine, constantly inventing new methods to evade the law and risking their lives to smuggle drugs.

